 <zboszor@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2026 11:30:14 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Move mutex_c out of ifdef in grib_context.cc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This fixes the build errors:

.../src/eccodes/grib_context.cc:217:57: error: 'mutex_c' was not declared in this scope; did you mean 'mutex'?
  217 |     eccodes::sync::LockGuard<eccodes::sync::Mutex> lock(mutex_c);
      |                                                         ^~~~~~~
      |                                                         mutex
.../src/eccodes/grib_context.cc: In function 'int grib_context_get_data_quality_checks(const grib_context*)':
.../src/eccodes/grib_context.cc:222:57: error: 'mutex_c' was not declared in this scope; did you mean 'mutex'?
  222 |     eccodes::sync::LockGuard<eccodes::sync::Mutex> lock(mutex_c);
      |                                                         ^~~~~~~
      |                                                         mutex

Signed-off-by: Zoltán Böszörményi <zboszor@gmail.com>
Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe specific]
---
 src/eccodes/grib_context.cc | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/eccodes/grib_context.cc b/src/eccodes/grib_context.cc
index 3e9aba96b..a453ec3bb 100644
--- a/src/eccodes/grib_context.cc
+++ b/src/eccodes/grib_context.cc
@@ -39,13 +39,12 @@ grib_string_list grib_file_not_found;
 #endif
 
 static eccodes::sync::Mutex mutex;
+static eccodes::sync::Mutex mutex_c;
 
 #if MANAGE_MEM
 
 #else
 
-static eccodes::sync::Mutex mutex_c;
-
 static void default_long_lasting_free(const grib_context* c, void* p)
 {
     free(p);
-- 
